         <abstract id="aspace_803cc8d49809f93038eb30b665a26c89">163 glass plate negatives of aerial photographs of oil fields in southern California by unidentified photographers, 1928-1931. 

Photographs were taken to locate and record existing oil well properties. Identified locations include Bakersfield, Fellows, Goleta, Kern Front Oil Field, Kettleman Hills, Lompoc, McKittrick, Midway-Sunset Oil Field, San Joaquin, Santa Ana, Santa Clara, and Santa Paula.

Circa 100 photographic prints (circa 1940s-1980s) and film negatives showing the same or similar views are also present.

Included is a 5 1/4-inch floppy disk.

Original envelopes for glass plates are included in the collection.</abstract>
